    <text id="R2215064T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>John Letcher, Governor of Virginia, writes Jefferson Davis in August, 1861, to
                    support the release of Dr. Washington Hilleary, held at Staunton for allegedly
                    aiding Union troops.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1861-08-14">AUGUST 14, 1861.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>His Excellency the PRESIDENT:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I am satisfied from my knowledge of Mr. Brannon, State senator from the district
                    in which Doctor Hilleary resides, and of Mr. Morrall, a resident also of the
                    district, that neither of them would ask for the release of an unfaithful or
                    disloyal man. Both of these gentlemen have been driven from their homes in
                    consequence of their loyalty and devotion to the cause of the South. Their
                    statement satisfy me that Doctor Hilleary has been improperly arrested and ought
                    to be discharged. He is confined at Staunton, Va.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>JOHN LETCHER.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
